<plot>Portuguese Man O' War is a cautionary story for all artists. It is a story of failure, disillusionment, self-deception, egotism, obsession, fear and complacency. It demonstrates how energy, ability and dedication can be diverted to utterly fruitless and hopelessly futile ends. This sad parable of wasted effort chronicles the troubling descent of an artist into despair, poverty and eternal isolation.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?440080</url></doc>
